2.00	Tom_Hooper_(ice_hockey)	Tom Hooper (ice hockey)	Charles Thomas Hooper (November 24, 1883 - March 24, 1960) was a Canadian professional ice hockey player. Hooper played for the Kenora Thistles, Montreal HC, and Montreal Wanderers. Hooper was a Stanley Cup winner with the Thistles in 1907 and the Wanderers in 1908. Noted for his skating speed, checking and stick-handling ability, he was inducted into the Hockey Hall of Fame in 1963.	
